**who —** THE NUCLEUS — a techne sphere — the art

**what —** At the centre of every atom, in a space a hundred thousand times smaller than the atom itself, protons and neutrons crowd together — held by the leftover edge of the strong force against the electric repulsion of the packed protons. Physicists model it as a liquid drop: a trembling, surface-tensioned ball. This sphere draws that drop in ink.

